            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1226.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Horace Darwin</ref> (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 22, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9234.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Horace Darwin, 9 January [1874]</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">The Macmillan bookshop was at 1 Trinity Street, Cambridge (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_3381.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Harrod &amp; Co.’s directory of Suffolk and Cambridgeshire</hi></ref> 1873).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">CD had been correcting <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> for a second edition since 20 November 1873 and had also been working on <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4097.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Insectivorous plants</hi></ref> (see ‘Journal’ (Appendix II)). A new edition of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1571.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Coral reefs</hi></ref>, published by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4407.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smith, Elder &amp; Co</ref>, appeared in June 1874 (<hi rend="italic">Publishers’ Circular</hi>, 1 July 1874, p. 420).</note>
